## API Style: {{ api_style }}

## Instructions
1. Generate a COMPLETE OpenAPI 3.1.0 YAML specification.
2. Include ALL CRUD endpoints implied by the class methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE).
3. Include request and response schemas as inline components under `components/schemas`.
4. For cross-service calls, use `$ref` with placeholder server URLs like `http://{{ dependency_name | lower }}-service:8080`.
5. Add an `x-internal-classes` extension at the top level listing the source class names.
6. Include a health check endpoint: `GET /health`.
7. Use meaningful HTTP status codes (200, 201, 400, 404, 500).
8. Add brief descriptions to all endpoints and schemas.

## Output
Return ONLY valid OpenAPI 3.1 YAML. No markdown fences, no prose, no explanation.
